I agree that it would be more idiomatic. I disagree that it is good.<p>Abstract classes have disjunctive semantics (logical OR) whereas interfaces have conjunctive semantics (logical AND).<p>The <i>actual important</i> thing that I wanted to capture is that an instance of Shape can only be one kind of shape at a time. With an interface a class could be more than one kind of Shape.<p><pre><code>    interface IFoo : IShape
    { 
        //some stuff
    }

    public class SomeShape : IShape, IFoo
    {
        //I am a circle AND a square!
    }</code></pre>
